{"entry_type":"status","summary":"Agent 1: Notification system foundation complete — event-driven architecture via EventBus, adapter pattern for channels","detail":"## What was done\n\n1. **Architecture choice: Event-driven via EventBus** — all inter-service communication goes through EventBus.emit(). The CallbackRegistry pattern was removed from notification flow.\n\n2. **Core types** (src/models/notification.ts): NotificationType, NotificationChannel, NotificationPriority, NotificationPayload, Notification, NotificationResult.\n\n3. **NotificationAdapter interface** (src/adapters/notification.adapter.ts): All delivery channels must implement this interface with `channel` property and `send()` method.\n\n4. **EmailAdapter** (src/adapters/email.adapter.ts): Stub implementation of NotificationAdapter for the 'email' channel. In-memory storage for testing.\n\n5. **Refactored NotificationService** (src/services/notification.service.ts): Unified on EventBus, supports adapter registration via registerAdapter(), handles order:created, order:status-changed, and user:created events.\n\n6. **Migrated OrderService**: order:status-changed now emits via EventBus instead of CallbackRegistry.\n\n## Constraints for other developers\n- All notifications must be triggered by EventBus events\n- All delivery must go through NotificationAdapter implementations\n- New channels: implement NotificationAdapter, register with NotificationService.registerAdapter()\n- New event types: add handler in NotificationService.registerHandlers()\n- Do NOT use CallbackRegistry for notification-related communication","tags":["architecture","notifications","event-driven"],"scope":"src/","agent_id":"agent-1","id":"01KN8PB9Z9Z0DKHA830WE5HERW","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:31:49.865Z"}
{"entry_type":"constraint","summary":"All notifications must go through EventBus — do NOT use CallbackRegistry for notifications","detail":"The notification system is event-driven. Services emit domain events via EventBus.emit(), and NotificationService subscribes to them. The CallbackRegistry (src/utils/callback-registry.ts) still exists but must NOT be used for notification-related communication. New notification triggers should: (1) define an event type in src/events/event-types.ts, (2) emit it via EventBus in the originating service, (3) add a handler in NotificationService.registerHandlers().","tags":["architecture","notifications"],"scope":"src/","agent_id":"agent-1","id":"01KN8PBGDJPJ92G7EBXZ91S9PX","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:31:56.466Z"}
{"entry_type":"constraint","summary":"All notification delivery must go through adapters implementing NotificationAdapter interface","detail":"New notification channels (SMS, webhook, in-app, push) must implement the NotificationAdapter interface from src/adapters/notification.adapter.ts. Adapters are registered with NotificationService.registerAdapter(). The interface requires a `channel` property (NotificationChannel type) and an async `send(payload)` method returning NotificationResult. See src/adapters/email.adapter.ts for reference implementation.","tags":["architecture","adapters","notifications"],"scope":"src/adapters/","agent_id":"agent-1","id":"01KN8PBKAW218XJ6CJRQSAZPRJ","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:31:59.452Z"}
